    narr:generatedFrom "d1b09a828565de86" ;
    narr:narration """This hub gathers per-document **phrasing assessments** from a rubric applied across pitches, calls, and plans. The through-line is consistent: strong idiolect, domain-specific verbs, and strategically deployed stock phrases that anchor themes and signal brand identity. Canonical product terms recur — [collective-memory / dollar-signs framing](narr:Assess_Phrasing_RevenueModelTAM), [continuation-machines and steering-vector vocabulary](narr:Rubric_Phrasing_ScarletDame), [compile/ingest/introspect verbs](narr:Rubric_Phrasing_PilotPlan). Memorable taglines do the load-bearing work: [\"The physics never changed. The substrate did\"](narr:RubricAssess_Phrasing), [\"gods of Olympus\" and \"MCP-native\"](narr:Rubric_Phrasing_FounderBetaUser), [\"separated at birth\" / \"I know Kung Fu\"](narr:Assessment_Phrasing_YC), [\"no one's selling that\"](narr:RubricAssess_Phrasing_WeeklyCall), and [\"builder trap\" / \"clean to sell\"](narr:RubricAssess_Phrasing_GTM). Across YC-facing material the [identity-and-chemistry phrasing](narr:Rubric_Phrasing_YC_Call) recurs, while strategic/financial docs lean on [domain terms like procurement threshold and retainer churn](narr:Assess_Phrasing_RevModel). No dates attach to these assessments; they read as a static evaluative layer, not a trajectory.""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Assess_Phrasing_RevModel> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Assess_Phrasing_RevenueModelTAM> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Assessment_Phrasing_YC> ;
